---
import BaseHead from '../components/BaseHead.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import { SITE_DESCRIPTION, SITE_TITLE } from '../consts';
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
	<head>
		<BaseHead title={SITE_TITLE} description={SITE_DESCRIPTION} />
	</head>
	<body>
		<Header />
		<main>
			<h1>Devmool</h1>
			<p><strong>Real code, real builds, real bugs — across the stack.</strong></p>
			<p>
				I build AI agents, full-stack apps, and distributed systems — and break them on
				camera. Every video has a writeup here with the code, the architecture, and the
				lessons I wish someone had told me.
			</p>
			<p>
				No "Top 10 AI tools" videos. No fluff. Just real engineering — Hinglish-friendly,
				code-first, honest about what works and what doesn't.
			</p>
			<p>What you'll find here:</p>
			<ul>
				<li>AI agents in production — LangGraph, RAG, multi-agent systems</li>
				<li>System design walkthroughs with real architectures</li>
				<li>Full-stack builds — Python, FastAPI, React, distributed systems</li>
				<li>The bugs, the fixes, and the lessons from shipping</li>
			</ul>
			<p>
				New post every 2 weeks. Each one comes with a
				<a href="https://youtube.com/@thedevmool">video on YouTube</a> and full code on
				<a href="https://github.com/thedevmool">GitHub</a>.
			</p>
			<p>
				👉 <a href="/blog">Read the latest posts</a><br />
				📺 <a href="https://youtube.com/@thedevmool">Watch on YouTube</a>
			</p>
		</main>
		<Footer />
	</body>
</html>
